From 7993f8436be298e3e4e648b5aea2751614d11bb5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: FIM43-Redeye <14264359+FIM43-Redeye@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Fri, 20 Feb 2026 19:49:08 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 2/3] LOCAL: TDR escalation via Secondary Bus Reset (SBR)

When soft recovery fails to unblock the NPU, escalate to a Secondary
Bus Reset on the upstream PCI bridge before declaring the device
unrecoverable.

Escalation model:
  counter 1  -> Soft recovery (existing stop/restart contexts)
  counter 2  -> SBR: tear down firmware, toggle bridge SBR bit,
                wait for link, restore PCI state, rebuild firmware
  counter 3+ -> Device declared unrecoverable, TDR stopped

The counter resets to 0 whenever the device resumes making progress.

SBR is done manually (pci_read/write_config_word on PCI_BRIDGE_CONTROL)
rather than through pci_reset_bus() to avoid requiring reset_prepare/
reset_done callbacks in the ops table, which AMD rejected for aie2.

Tested: setpci-based manual SBR on bus c6 (bridge 00:08.2) confirmed
the device comes back clean on Phoenix/Hawk Point hardware.
